{
  "texts": [
    "Trust in accounts is modeled by the reshare network (top); trust in sources can be modeled by the bipartite account-source network (middle), or a projection of it, the co-share networks (bottom).",
    "Colors represent credibility labels: orange and purple for high-and low-credibility, respectively Figure 22Figure 2Retweet network constructed from the Twitter_Covid dataset.",
    "To visualize the network, we filter nodes and edges using k-core decomposition[58] (k = 3).",
    "Colors represent credibility score: orange and purple for high-and low-credibility accounts, respectively, and gray for unlabeled accounts.",
    "Node size represents in-strength, i.e., the number of retweets by the account."
  ]
}